How to build Debian packages (e.g. for fpart version 1.1.0) :
*************************************************************

1) Firt, install required tools:

# apt-get install build-essential curl debhelper automake dh-autoreconf

2) Clone (and/or) update fpart repository:

$ git clone 'https://github.com/martymac/fpart.git'

$ cd fpart
$ git checkout master
$ git pull

$ cp -R contribs/package/debian .
$ git checkout fpart-1.1.0
$ curl 'http://contribs.martymac.org/fpart/fpart-1.1.0.tar.gz' > ../fpart_1.1.0.orig.tar.gz

3) Build source and binary packages:

$ dpkg-source -b .
$ dpkg-buildpackage -us -us -b
